FFC Capital Markets® is a securities and investment banking firm that provides
 a range of financial services to a substantial and diverse client base that includes high-net-worth individuals and families, corporations, financial institutions, and public agencies.

Key features & benefits to FFC Capital Markets® clients:


Access to diverse group of experienced, solution driven, investment and finance professionals
Account access and administration via internet
Customized asset management and investment banking solutions for private wealth, industry and government
Significant socio economic impact to Louisiana centric communities through 1) provision of creative finance solutions to infrastructure needs and 2) optimal performance
 strategies for public and private capital (cash and securities) assets. 


INVESTMENT BANKING
We offer a range of investment banking services to corporations, non-profits, public agencies, and state and local governments. Our services include strategic and financial advisory assignments
 primarily with respect to municipal finance and risk management as well as debt and equity private placements.

INSTITUTIONAL CLIENT SERVICES
We facilitate transactions in fixed income, equity, currency and commodity products, primarily with institutional investors such as banks, insurance companies, investment funds, family
 offices and state and local governments. 

PRIVATE WEALTH & RETIREMENT ADVISORY
We provide private wealth and retirement advisory services, including portfolio management, financial counseling, estate planning, pension planning, insurance and other traditional financial
 services to high-net-worth individuals, families and small business owners.

DISCRETIONARY & OUTSOURCED INVESTMENT MANAGEMENT 
For bond proceeds, debt service reserves, general and project funds to total portfolios that utilize both traditional and alternative asset classes, we have an investment solution that
 will work for you.  

We deliver tailored investment management and wrap fee program solutions on a transparent, full-disclosure basis via a separately managed account (SMA) format. 

We provide a full array of portfolio supervisory (Outsourced CIO) services  including strategy & document development, manager search & selection, detailed security & portfolio level performance measurement of third-party investment managers and products covering
 both traditional and alternative asset classes to a diverse set of clients including insurance companies, defined benefit pension sponsors, foundations & endowments, high-net-worth individuals and families.





























