FFC Capital Management (FFCCM) is a globally resourced 40 Act SEC registered investment
 advisor (RIA) founded in January 2001. Principals of the company began investment consulting practice in 1996 while executives with Prudential Securities. FFCCM is a 16 year old, independent employee-owned
limited liability company.
On December 14, 2011 FINRA granted membership status to FFC Capital Advisors, LLC (FFCCA), a separate legal entity. FFCCA is a broker dealer
 affiliate of FFCCM; and was formed to facilitate services not in conflict with the delivery of FFCCM’s advisory or fiduciary level services. Specifically, FFCCA is an investment bank focused on public finance, bond trading and asset management. Through FFCCM
 and FFCCA, we are proud to offer total portfolio asset management, liability-driven investment advisory and financial consulting services to individuals, family offices public funds, corporations, institutional non-profits, and small businesses.
Our professional staff boasts in excess of 15 years average industry related experience, while our principals average in excess of 25 years
 of industry related practice. Including our roles as individual trustees, FFC and its principals act as fiduciaries to in excess of $1 billion in public and private liability driven assets. 

































