Community Impact

Whether its capital funding for higher education, improving public school facilities, maintaining bridges & roads, replacing water & drainage systems or building airport terminals,
 both public and private institutions require financing to address their most pressing infrastructure needs.

FFC Capital is committed to supporting these issuers in building the communities we live, and work in ... to maintain and improve the quality of life, particularly in Louisiana and the Gulf Coast regions. 








Environmental Commitment

At FFC Capital Markets, we take full advantage of the technology at our disposal. We send information to our clients electronically whenever possible to deliver real time data while decreasing
 our environmental impact. We also encourage our clients to enroll in paperless statements. Printing is available to our clients upon request or only as needed. 









Transparency & Ethics 

As an SEC Registered Investment Advisor (RIA) & Registered Municipal Securities Advisor (MA), FFC Capital Markets has as its main duty to at all times place the interests of our clients first.
 In order to maintain only ethical activity, we have adopted a Code of Ethics (“The Code”). All personnel must acknowledge and adhere-to the provisions therein annually or as amended.
































